text.tspan: Opium poppy cultivation in Afghanistan reached a sobering record high in 2013. According to the 2013
Afghanistan Opium Survey, cultivation amounted to some 209,000 hectares, outstripping the earlier
record in 2007 of 193,000 hectares, and representing a 36% increase over 2012.
